<concept id="concept_u4h_lwt_ls">
 <title>Using an HDFS User</title>
 <conbody>
  <p><indexterm>Hadoop FS destination<indexterm>using an HDFS user to write to
        Hadoop</indexterm></indexterm><ph
        conref="../Reusable_Content/ReusablePhrases.dita#concept_vhs_5tz_xp/HUser-Intro"/>
      destination to write to HDFS. </p>
    <p conref="../Reusable_Content/ReusablePhrases.dita#concept_vhs_5tz_xp/HUser-ImpProperty"/>
    <p>Note that the destination <ph
        conref="../Reusable_Content/ReusablePhrases.dita#concept_vhs_5tz_xp/HUser-ConnectUser"
        /><draft-comment author="Loretta">Make sure updates to this topic go into the origin version
        of this file. And possibly the HBase version?</draft-comment></p>
  <p>To configure a user in the destination to write to HDFS, perform the following tasks:<ol
                id="ul_mb1_xpt_ls">
                <li conref="../Reusable_Content/ReusablePhrases.dita#concept_vhs_5tz_xp/HUser-Step1"/>
                <li>In the Hadoop FS destination, on the <wintitle>Hadoop FS</wintitle> tab,
                    configure the <uicontrol>HDFS User</uicontrol> property.</li>
            </ol></p>
 </conbody>
</concept>
